TeamFlow Project Report
1. Project Overview

TeamFlow is a full-stack Project Management and Team Collaboration System developed to help software teams efficiently manage projects, tasks, comments, attachments, notifications, and user profiles from a single platform.

The application follows a secure client-server architecture using Spring Boot for the backend, React for the frontend, and MySQL for data storage. Authentication is implemented using JWT, while role-based authorization ensures secure access to project resources.

2. System Architecture

The application follows a three-tier architecture.

Presentation Layer

React
Tailwind CSS
Axios
React Router

Business Layer

Spring Boot
Spring Security
JWT Authentication
REST APIs

Data Layer

MySQL
Spring Data JPA
Hibernate

This architecture improves maintainability, scalability, and separation of concerns.

3. Database Design

The database consists of the following primary entities:

Users
Projects
Tasks
Comments
Attachments
Notifications
Project Members
Activity Logs
Task Relations

Relationships are implemented using JPA with proper foreign key constraints.

4. Security

Security features include:

JWT Authentication
Password Encryption using BCrypt
Role-Based Authorization
Protected REST APIs
Secure Request Validation

Two user roles are supported:

ADMIN
MEMBER

Administrators can manage projects and tasks, while members have restricted access

5. Major Features
User Registration and Login
Dashboard Analytics
Project Management
Task Management
Comments
Attachments
Notifications
Profile Management
Dark and Light Theme
Swagger API Documentation
Responsive User Interface

6. Design Decisions

The following design decisions were made during implementation:

Spring Boot was selected for rapid backend development.
React was used to create a responsive user interface.
MySQL provides reliable relational data storage.
JWT enables stateless authentication.
REST APIs separate frontend and backend responsibilities.
Layered Architecture improves maintainability.
Role-Based Authorization secures sensitive operations.

7. Future Improvements

Future enhancements include:

Email Notifications
Kanban Board
Calendar View
Cloud File Storage
Team Chat
Activity Timeline
Docker Deployment
CI/CD Pipeline
Cloud Hosting
Mobile Application

8. Conclusion

TeamFlow successfully demonstrates the implementation of a secure, scalable, and modern project management platform using Spring Boot, React, and MySQL. The project follows software engineering best practices and provides a strong foundation for future enhancements.